Racing Club di Aruba Trip to Venezuela 1947

Both matches were played at Estadio Nacional in Caracas.

[November 8]
Unión Sport Club         6-1      Racing Club di Aruba
  [Umaña 25, 33, 46, 53, Alberto “Cañón” Casco 17, 70; Keelboom 40]
  [Unión: Miguel “Pez Volador” Sanabria, Alejandro Mariscotti (Argentinian),
     Eduardo Fenton (Guerrieri), David Zamudio, Nerio “La Venadita” Seijas
     (Soria, Peruvian), Vargas (Guardia), Pedro “Estrellita” Terán, Umaña
     (Costarrican), Alberto “Cañón” Casco (Argentinian), Sixto Soler
     (Peruvian), Vargas (Peruvian);
   RCA: Reyes, Tromp, Brokke, Fingaal, Tromp, Kelly (Kelli), Beerken,
    Jansen, Keljboom, Chirinos, Broca; 
   Ref: Arcia Cazañas (Venezuela)]

[November 9]
La Salle                 6-4      Racing Club di Aruba
  [Campos 2, 7, Alfonso Odría 56, 63, Otero 35, 49; Chas 20, Brokka 72,
   Chirinos 75, 80]
  [La Salle: Policarpio “Piolín” Espejo (Zúñiga, Peruvian or Costarican),
    “Indio” Vega, Moleiro (Jahn Arnal), Reinaldo Cámera, Otero, Vicente
    “Vicentico” Fernández, Asdrúbal “Quemao” Olivares, Delfín Benítez
    Cáceres (Paraguayan), Campos (Anco, Peruvian?), Alfonso Odría (Peruvian),
    Del Real;
   RCA: Reyes (Hoolsboum), Tromp, Broca, Fingaal, Broca, Kelly, Jensen,
    Chas, Kelkboom, Chirinos, Broca;
   Ref: Benito Jackson (Venezuela)]


